<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy — Code-Rescue"
  description="Code-Rescue collects no personal data from site visitors. No analytics, no cookies, no tracking."
  kicker="Privacy"
  h1="Privacy Policy"
  lastUpdated="April 24, 2026"
>
  <h2>Short version</h2>
  <p>
    This website collects nothing from you. No cookies. No analytics. No tracking pixels. No
    third-party scripts. No fingerprinting. No server logs beyond what the CDN automatically retains
    for abuse prevention.
  </p>

  <h2>What the site actually does</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Serves static HTML, CSS, and a tiny amount of JavaScript from Cloudflare Pages.</li>
    <li>
      Loads three fonts (Newsreader, JetBrains Mono, Inter) <em>self-hosted from this domain</em> — no
      Google Fonts request, no third-party font CDN.
    </li>
    <li>
      Renders a live clock in the footer via a 15-line script that runs entirely in your browser and
      transmits nothing.
    </li>
    <li>
      Publishes a machine-readable engagement summary at
      <a href="/.well-known/engagements.json">/.well-known/engagements.json</a> for agents.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What the site does not do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Set any cookie of any kind.</li>
    <li>Load Google Analytics, Plausible, PostHog, Mixpanel, Segment, or any analytics service.</li>
    <li>Load Facebook Pixel, LinkedIn Insight Tag, Twitter/X, or any advertising pixel.</li>
    <li>Use session replay, heat maps, or any behavioral-tracking tool.</li>
    <li>Embed any third-party script, iframe, or beacon.</li>
    <li>Collect your IP, user-agent, or referrer into any log we retain.</li>
    <li>Fingerprint your browser, device, or network.</li>
    <li>Sell, share, rent, or transmit any data about you to anyone.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When you email</h2>
  <p>
    If you email <a href="mailto:max@code-rescue.com">max@code-rescue.com</a>, that email lives in
    an inbox operated by Maxwell Collins. It's read by him. It's replied to by him. It is not
    shared, sold, or processed by any automated marketing system.
  </p>

  <h2>When you book a call</h2>
  <p>
    The booking flow at <a href="https://www.code-rescue.com/book/">code-rescue.com/book/</a> is operated
    by a third-party scheduling tool. That tool has its own privacy policy. The only information captured
    is the information you type into the form.
  </p>

  <h2>Cloudflare logs</h2>
  <p>
    Cloudflare — the CDN that serves this site — retains standard edge logs (request IP, timestamp,
    URL, status code) for up to 7 days for abuse prevention. Those logs are not accessible to
    Code-Rescue, are not correlated with any other data, and are purged automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    There is no account to delete, no profile to update, no preferences to unset, because there is
    no data to delete, update, or unset. If you're reading this page to make sure nobody is tracking
    you: nobody here is. If you'd like to verify that independently, open devtools and watch the
    Network tab while you browse the site. The only requests are to
    <code>code-rescue.com</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If this policy changes, the "Last updated" date at the top of this page changes. If a change
    ever added tracking, analytics, or cookies, it would be called out at the top of the page under
    a header explicitly labeled "What changed."
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions: <a href="mailto:max@code-rescue.com">max@code-rescue.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
